===============================================================PG ADMIN=============================================================================================

==============================================================DATABASE CREATION=====================================================================================
1. Open PgAdmin
2. Expand "servers"
3. Click "Localhost", it will ask for password. (ex: Bhuva1102)
4. Right click "Databases", then click "Create"-> "Database"
5. Fill the fields:
	Database: talksy
	Owner: leave as postgres (default)
6. Click Save

```````ðŸŽ‰ Database created successfully.`````````````

==============================================================TABLE CREATION=======================================================================================
1. Open Query Tool

	1.1 Expand:
	  Databases â†’ talksy
	1.2 Right-click on talksy
	1.3 Click Query Tool

```````ðŸŽ‰ This opens an SQL editor.`````````````

2. Create "users" Table

	2.1 Paste this SQL into the Query Tool:
		CREATE TABLE users (
		  id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
		  username VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
		  email VARCHAR(150) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
		  password_hash VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
		  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
		);

	2.2 Now click the â–¶ Execute button (or press F5).
	2.3You should see:
```````âœ… Query returned successfully````````````

